content.text:
Introduced in C++11, `enum class` (scoped enums) are safer than traditional enums because their values are scoped and do not implicitly convert to integers. The syntax is:
enum class EnumName { value1, value2, value3 };
Scoped enums require `EnumName::value` to access values.

